http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Louisiana State Physical Education Standards are based on the National Physical Education Standards developed by the National Association for Sport and Physical Education. This standards document is not a state curriculum or a predetermined course of study; rather, it speaks of competencies, defining what a student should know and be able to do. Teachers in the state of Louisiana are encouraged and empowered to create their own physical education curriculum that would best help their students meet these standards.
